  "prompt": "If somebody is smoking weed around me, is it possible to get high off of second hand smoke?",
  "response": "It is possible to detect THC in the blood from secondhand marijuana smoke, but getting noticeably high from it is unlikely under normal circumstances. A study published in the journal Drug and Alcohol Dependence found that while THC could be detected in the blood of non-smokers exposed to secondhand marijuana smoke in an unventilated room, the levels were very low and participants did not report feeling high.\n\nTo experience significant psychoactive effects from secondhand smoke, you would need to be in an enclosed, unventilated space with heavy marijuana use for an extended period. In typical social situations with normal ventilation, the amount of THC you would inhale from secondhand smoke is not enough to produce a noticeable high.",
